        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gemini): bridge OAuth profiles into CLI runtime",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- opt `google-gemini-cli` into explicit OpenClaw auth-profile forwarding\n- refresh/load the selected OAuth profile before CLI backend preparation\n- materialize selected Gemini OAuth credentials into an isolated `GEMINI_CLI_HOME/.gemini/oauth_creds.json` for the `gemini` subprocess\n- keep Gemini CLI auth epochs profile-owned when the bridge is active\n\nFixes #88742.\n\n## Proof\n\nHEAD: `30006c059f1cc4656aed1eeecf5b2ecff8b40c48`\n\nValidation log: `/tmp/openclaw-pr88742-validation.log`\n\nCommands:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/google/setup-api.test.ts src/agents/cli-backends.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts --reporter=dot\npnpm -s exec oxfmt --check extensions/google/cli-backend.ts extensions/google/setup-api.test.ts src/agents/cli-backends.test.ts src/agents/cli-backends.ts src/agents/cli-runner/prepare.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.ts src/plugin-sdk/cli-backend.ts src/plugins/cli-backend.types.ts src/plugins/types.ts\npnpm -s exec oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/agents/cli-backends.test.ts src/agents/cli-backends.ts src/agents/cli-runner/prepare.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.ts src/plugin-sdk/cli-backend.ts src/plugins/cli-backend.types.ts src/plugins/types.ts extensions/google/cli-backend.ts extensions/google/setup-api.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nRelevant output:\n\n```text\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  59 passed (59)\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  3 passed (3)\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n```\n\nSource-level behavior proof: `/tmp/openclaw-pr88742-proof.log`\n\n- `extensions/google/setup-api.test.ts` proves selected OAuth credentials produce an isolated Gemini CLI home and writes `.gemini/oauth_creds.json` without logging token material.\n- `src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts` proves canonical `google/*` models routed through `google-gemini-cli` select the `google-gemini-cli:*` auth profile before `runCliAgent`.\n\nNot tested:\n\n- No live Gemini OAuth subprocess run with a disposable Google account in this PR.\n- Full `pnpm -s exec tsgo --noEmit` is blocked on current HEAD by pre-existing errors outside this patch:\n\n```text\nsrc/config/io.ts(192,7): error TS2527: The inferred type of 'configWritePostCommitRollback' references an inaccessible 'unique symbol' type. A type annotation is necessary.\nsrc/secrets/config-io.ts(8,17): error TS4058: Return type of exported function has or is using name 'configWritePostCommitRollback' from external module \".../src/config/io\" but cannot be named.\n```\n\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: `google-gemini-cli` execution receives the selected OpenClaw `google-gemini-cli:*` OAuth profile through an isolated `GEMINI_CLI_HOME/.gemini/oauth_creds.json`, instead of relying on ambient Gemini CLI home state.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local Linux workstation, PR branch `fix/88742-gemini-cli-oauth-bridge`, head `0950e599f9c515abaf60a60bf359a958ce93ab16`, OpenClaw repository checkout, Node subprocess execution through the Gemini CLI backend command path. Token and account identifiers were redacted.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```text\ncd /home/rev/projects/openclaw-prs/pr-88742-gemini-cli-oauth-bridge\ncreated conflicting ambient HOME/.gemini/oauth_creds.json\ncreated controlled gemini subprocess executable on PATH\nran: pnpm -s exec tsx \"/tmp/openclaw-pr88748-real-proof-1780258617/run-gemini-bridge-proof.mjs\"\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n\n```text\nPRE_EXEC_PROOF {\n  \"hasGeminiCliHome\": true,\n  \"stagedHomeBasename\": \"gemini-cli-home-xGNkmi\",\n  \"stagedAccessMatchesSelectedProfile\": true,\n  \"stagedRefreshMatchesSelectedProfile\": true,\n  \"stagedAccessMatchesAmbientHome\": false,\n  \"stagedRefreshMatchesAmbientHome\": false\n}\nSUBPROCESS_STDOUT {\n  \"subprocess\": \"gemini\",\n  \"sawGeminiCliHome\": true,\n  \"stagedHomeBasename\": \"gemini-cli-home-xGNkmi\",\n  \"selectedAccessUsed\": true,\n  \"selectedRefreshUsed\": true,\n  \"ambientAccessUsed\": false,\n  \"ambientRefreshUsed\": false,\n  \"argv\": [\n    \"--skip-trust\",\n    \"--output-format\",\n    \"json\",\n    \"--prompt\",\n    \"{prompt}\"\n  ]\n}\nSUBPROCESS_STDERR \nSUBPROCESS_EXIT 0\nCLEANUP_PROOF {\n  \"cleanupRemovedHome\": true\n}\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: The Gemini subprocess saw `GEMINI_CLI_HOME`, read credentials from the isolated OpenClaw-created Gemini home, used the selected OpenClaw profile canaries, did not use the conflicting ambient `HOME/.gemini` canaries, and cleanup removed the temporary Gemini home.\n- **What was not tested**: No real Google token, refresh token, ID token, or private Google account identifier is included in the proof. The subprocess executable is controlled locally so token routing can be verified without disclosing real OAuth material.\n",
